///
/// THEOREM: atomic_update
///
/// For a symbol table with generation counter, an atomic CAS update ensures
/// that every thread observes either the old or new code, never a mixture.
///
/// Proof sketch:
/// 1. Generation counter is atomic (CPU-level CAS)
/// 2. All lookups check generation before dereferencing
/// 3. Old code can only be reached via generation <= old_gen
/// 4. New code reachable only after CAS succeeds
/// 5. Therefore: no race window, no mixing
///
